# Line endings are normalised to LF in the repository and on checkout,
# on every platform.
#
# Without this, git applies core.autocrlf on Windows and converts text files to
# CRLF at checkout. gofmt normalises to LF, so a CRLF working tree makes
# `gofmt -l` list every Go file as unformatted — which failed CI on the Windows
# runner while passing on Linux, for reasons invisible in the source.
#
# Forcing LF also keeps the shell scripts embedded in the workflow files
# executable, and stops diffs showing whole-file changes when contributors work
# on different platforms.
* text=auto eol=lf

# Content that must never be line-ending converted.
*.png  binary
*.jpg  binary
*.jpeg binary
*.gif  binary
*.ico  binary
*.pdf  binary
*.xlsx binary
*.zip  binary
*.exe  binary
